o of royal dutch shell plc from july  to december  he started his career at royal dutch shell in  working in a number of finance and business roles in different countries between  and  he served as chief financial officer for abb in  he was appointed shell’s chief financial officer cfo and then ceo in july  in april  he was elected as chairman of abbs board of directors contents  early life  career  personal life  awards  critics  references  external links early lifeedit voser was born in baden switzerland in  from  to  he studied for a business administration degree from zurich university of applied sciences switzerland careeredit in  at age  voser joined shell and held a variety of finance and business roles in switzerland the uk argentina and chile as well as chief financial officer of oil products from  to  voser was cfo and an executive committee member of the asea brown boveri abb group of companies voser is active in a number of international and bilateral organisations including the european round table of industrialists and the business council in  he became a director of catalyst a nonprofit organisation working to build inclusive environments and expand opportunities for women at work in  he joined the board of directors of leading swiss healthcare research company roche on  may  it was announced that voser would retire from the company in the first half of  on  july  ibm selected him as one of the board of directors for the company on  january  voser was appointed to the board of directors of temasek holdings on  april  voser was elected as chairman of the board of directors of abb personal lifeedit voser is married to daniela and has three children since september  he has been serving in the position of the chairman of the st gallen foundation for international studies replacing josef ackermann awardsedit in july  his majesty the sultan of brunei awarded voser the title of dato seri laila jasa in recognition of his services to brunei criticsedit royal 