m as previously announced and all other members of the board will stand for reelection shareholders will vote on the proposed changes on april   “i am delighted that peter voser has accepted to stand for election as chairman of abb” hubertus von grünberg said “peter voser brings intimate knowledge of abb and its key markets as well as an excellent track record as a leader in large global organizations” shareholders elect board members for a oneyear term and will vote on the nominations at the agm on april   the board intends to elect jacob wallenberg as vicechairman of the board after the agm von grünberg has been chairman of the abb board since may  during his tenure abb’s revenues have risen from about  billion in  to  billion in  whilst net income has doubled under his leadership abb also achieved an unprecedented global balance in its business across europe the americas asiamiddle east and africa in his time as chairman abb launched many breakthrough innovations including a breaker for highvoltage direct current hvdc the revolutionary humanmachine collaborative robot yumi and emax the world’s first lowvoltage circuit breaker that also functions as an energy manager michael treschow chairman of the governance and nomination committee joined the abb board in  and has contributed strongly to the company’s return to profitable growth with his wealth of industrial leadership experience in key markets of abb in addition to hubertus von grünberg the current members of the abb board are roger agnelli matti alahuhta louis r hughes michel de rosen michael treschow jacob wallenberg and ying yeh “i am honored to be nominated as chairman of the board and look forward to working with abb’s ceo ulrich spiesshofer his executive team and the board of directors to drive accelerated sustainable value creation through the implementation of the recently announced next level strategy” said peter voser peter voser a swiss citizen was ceo of royal dutch shell one of the world’s largest companies from  to the end of  prior to this he served as chief financial officer cfo of royal dutch shell between  and  voser worked for shell and served in a number of finance and business roles in switzerland the uk argentina and chile between  and october  peter voser was cfo of abb ltd and a key leader behind the successful turnaround and repositioning of the company for longterm profitable growth voser also brings a wealth of experience as a board member of publicly listed companies such as roche ubs until  and aegon until  abb wwwabbcom is a leader in power and automation technologies that enable utility and industry customers to improve their performance and lower their environmental impact the abb group of companies operates in more than  countries and employs about  people stay in the loop search news only rate this page positive negative thank you for your feedback positive negative your comments email  contact information optional   cancel share this page twitter facebook linkedin weibo print email your email address you must enter one valid email address send to email address you must enter one valid email address please type one email address only your personal note you must enter a message   cancel contact us media relations thomas schmidt antonio ligizurich switzerlandtel     investor relations switzerland tel      attachments press release english version pdf press release german version pdf peter voser cv peter voser portrait peter voser portrait  provider informationimpressum  copyright  abbcookies and privacy policylogin facebooktwitter seitp accceecdb peter r voser  former chief executive officer at royal dutch shell plc news home advertising board and executive moves energy health care hedge funds m  a private equity technology you have    free profiles   left this month    start your free trial ➤ hey we noticed youre a relsci pro subscriber would you like to view the page there view on relsci pro ➤ email linkedin facebook google tweet reddit 